{
  "texts": [
    "Inconsistent Label Sourcing.",
    "Another source of between-dataset variation, is the source of misinformation labels.",
    "While most datasets rely on domain experts, some use lay volunteers to verify content, either explicitly (CREDBANK (Mitra and Gilbert 2015), WEIBO15 (Ma et al. 2016), WEIBO17 (Jin et al. 2017)) or implicitly (SOME LIKE IT HOAX (Tacchini et al. 2017)).",
    "Recently, datasets have started using many misinformation sources (FAKECOVID (Shahi and Nandini 2020), MUMIN (Nielsen et al. 2022), MCFEND (Li et al. 2024)).",
    "These can come from different countries and cultures, some of which are likely to disagree on their misinformation definitions."
  ]
}